    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>OpenIntro builds inference from the sampling distribution of the sample proportion, then generalizes. We use the sample mean for clarity. The original covers decision errors with medical testing analogies and uses simulation to build intuition for sampling distributions. For large samples, the Z-test is equivalent to the t-test. Small-sample inference uses the t-distribution (covered in Ch. 7).</p>

